 tower.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           ùA letter rests on this desk. It reads: 'Jredlol, chief stonemason, know that we must abandon our most beautiful creation, the ivory towers, and build dwellings in the caves. We must take refuge from the coming storm and rebuild after it has passed.'      ò'Of course the first thing that must be carved from our brother stones must be a new shrine to Domnu. Follow these preliminary drawings. We have driven the red claws from the cave networks, but design reinforced entrances should they return.'             $You take the architectural drawings.                                                                                                                                                                                                                           òA heavily armed Defender awaits you in this secret room. He has gathered some of his cohorts to him for a final showdown. 'At them', he cries 'for the Master.' They engage you. You notice they are backed up by large canine featured humanoids.             LSome gatesmen strike a brass gong as you pass but do not interfere with you.                                                                                                                                                                                   iAnother gong is sounded as you pass these gates. The gatesmen appear to be looking everywhere but at you.                                                                                                                                                      ‰This squat church hasn't been kept up in recent weeks. Weeds grow around the entranceway and the doors hang open. There is no one inside.                                                                                    