a world becomes when the Grey God has achieved victory. Not a single soul to harvest nor child's nightmare to collect.' He sighs.                            õ'I doubt we'll meet again. I will have to grow another body. It could take hundreds of years.' He glowers at you, then grins impishly again. 'Unless ...' His eyes widen as he snaps his overlarge mouth shut. His image begins to shimmer and waver.          And he is gone.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                üYou launch an attack at this creature of pure malice. It passes straight through him. He mimics being thrown back and clutches at his chest in a bout of overacting. He laughs, 'Fools, I lost my body, don't you remember? I am just a shade here. Listen.'   ]There is a pull at your mind. An alien presence is trying to penetrate your thought process.                                                                                                                                                                   The feeling continues ... even stronger now. Suddenly the presence recedes from your mind. However, a clear impression is left...                                                                                                                              ²This strange crystalline dwelling stands in stark contrast to its nightmarish surroundings. It is a thing of grace and beauty around which the grotesque forest has left a glade.                                                                              ÄYou enter and see what looks like a wisp of prismatic light dancing around the room in some sort of rhythm. A probing sensation enters your minds once more. You experience another thought-message.                                                           JThe light slows down to a soft hum and then slowly winks out of existence.                                                                                                                                                                                     ŸThe thick blood oozes and pops. It boils violently at your approach and then seems to eject globs of vileness into the air. The globs take shape and advance...                                                                                                RA cairn lies here, lying like a scab amidst the channels of blood. Open the cairn?                                                                                                                                                                             –A revolting nether beast springs out of the opening as if desperate to be freed of its confines. It gazes upon you hungrily and attacks with a bellow.                                                                                                         ¯The Pattern falls silent. The blood starts to flow more like a normal river, toward the sea. As the blood thins out, you notice something in the southeast part of the Pattern.                                                                                vA strange fragile structure is revealed once the blood flows from this depression. There is an entrance. Do you enter?                                                                                                                                         QAfter a barely tangible feeling of movement you find yourself in front of a ship.                                                                                                                                                                              ÈThis tortured plane of existence begins to unravel without its 'master.' You find yourselves violently ejected from it only to arrive in the Shadowgaunt's stronghold in front of the now consumed rift.                                                       You leave the stronghold.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      7Monstrous bats are attracted to the motion of the boat!                                                                                                                                                                                                        ©A revolting nether beast springs out of the opening as if desperate to be freed of its confines. It gazes upon you, summons some of its kin, and then moves to swarm you.                                                                                      ½For an instant you sense that a being of immense power has cast his gaze upon you. You are left with a lasting impression, as if your retinas had been burned by staring too long at the sun.                                                                  2If they are listening ... you would never know it.                                                                                                                                                                                                             MOn the edge of the ice sits a hut. An ancient frost giant can be seen inside.                                                                                                                                                                                  